# Template for python-appimage's requirements.txt (see build.sh, which
# copies this file and appends an absolute path to the repo checkout — the
# actual requirements.txt is generated per-build and gitignored, since that
# last line is machine-specific).
#
# Only the CLI's own dependencies + the engine it wraps. PyGObject (the GUI's
# only extra) is deliberately NOT here — see docs/PACKAGING.md, "Why the
# AppImage is CLI-only".
# No spaces in any line below: python-appimage's own requirement-install
# step runs each line through `shell=True` unquoted (utils/system.py), so
# PEP 508 "name @ url" specifiers get word-split and break pip. The bare
# VCS-URL form (no "gamma-launcher @ " prefix) is space-free and pip infers
# the package name from it just fine.
